The paper discusses the problem of diagram interpretation and reasoning, which involves understanding the structure and semantics of diagrams. This is a task that falls under the domain of computer vision and natural language processing, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Given that the paper focuses on using deep learning models for diagram parsing and question answering, it is most likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. However, it also involves aspects of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR), as it deals with understanding and processing complex information in diagrams.
